LOCUS       Ulp1                     219 aa            linear   UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  Catalytic domain (residues 403-621) of S. cerevisiae Ulp1 (UniProt
            Q02724), the SUMO/Smt3-specific cysteine protease that cleaves after
            the SUMO C-terminal di-glycine to release a native N-terminus;
            cognate protease of the SUMO fusion tag..
