     CDS             1..219
                     /label="Ulp1"
                     /synonym="Ulp1 protease"
                     /synonym="SUMO protease"
                     /synonym="Smt3-specific protease"
                     /note="Catalytic (UD/Ulp) domain of Saccharomyces
                     cerevisiae Ulp1, residues 403-621 of the 621-aa UniProt
                     Q02724 (ULP1_YEAST). SUMO/Smt3-specific cysteine protease
                     (clan CE, SENP/Ulp family) that cleaves after the SUMO
                     C-terminal Gly-Gly to release a passenger with a native
                     (scarless) N-terminus. This minimal catalytic fragment is
                     the canonical 403-621 crystallography/expression construct
                     (PDB 1EUV) and is sufficient for the essential
                     SUMO-deconjugation function in vivo."
